---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
---

<Layout
  title="About"
  description="How JobScope curates practical, experience-based career stories."
>
  <section class="page-hero about-hero animate-rise">
    <p><strong>Inside JobScope</strong></p>
    <h1>Built like a field guide, not a brochure.</h1>
    <p>
      Most career resources explain titles. JobScope documents lived work reality: what people do,
      where they struggle, what gets better with experience, and what students should know before
      committing years to a path.
    </p>
  </section>

  <section class="signal-strip" aria-label="JobScope signal strip">
    <p><span>Signal 01</span> Real workflows over abstract job descriptions</p>
    <p><span>Signal 02</span> Honest tradeoffs, not hype</p>
    <p><span>Signal 03</span> Student-first recommendations</p>
  </section>

  <section class="origin-grid">
    <div class="origin-story panel">
      <p class="kicker">Why this exists</p>
      <h2>Students are asked to choose early with incomplete information.</h2>
      <p>
        We kept seeing the same pattern: people select degrees, internships, or transitions based on
        polished summaries, then discover the real day-to-day too late. JobScope exists to close
        that gap with structured first-person reporting.
      </p>
      <blockquote>Better choices come from concrete stories, not generic career advice.</blockquote>
    </div>

    <aside class="review-panel panel" aria-label="Editorial review model">
      <h2>Editorial review model</h2>
      <dl>
        <div>
          <dt>What we publish</dt>
          <dd>Detailed day-to-day tasks, clear tradeoffs, and practical advice to students.</dd>
        </div>
        <div>
          <dt>What we reject</dt>
          <dd>Vague promotion, empty takes, or submissions without actionable detail.</dd>
        </div>
        <div>
          <dt>Identity options</dt>
          <dd>Contributors can submit publicly or anonymously. Both are clearly labeled.</dd>
        </div>
      </dl>
    </aside>
  </section>

  <section class="compass panel" aria-label="JobScope editorial compass">
    <p class="kicker">Our compass</p>
    <h2>Every approved story should answer four practical questions.</h2>
    <div class="compass-grid">
      <article>
        <h3>What does the week actually look like?</h3>
        <p>Meetings, tools, deliverables, collaboration rhythm.</p>
      </article>
      <article>
        <h3>What feels rewarding?</h3>
        <p>Moments that make people stay in the role long-term.</p>
      </article>
      <article>
        <h3>What is genuinely hard?</h3>
        <p>Stress points, limitations, and difficult parts of the work.</p>
      </article>
      <article>
        <h3>Who is this path a fit for?</h3>
        <p>Specific advice for students and career switchers.</p>
      </article>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="lifecycle" aria-label="Submission lifecycle">
    <p class="kicker">How stories move through JobScope</p>
    <ol>
      <li>
        <strong>Submit:</strong> contributors complete a structured form with required practical fields.
      </li>
      <li>
        <strong>Moderate:</strong> staff reviews quality, tone, and trust criteria before approval.
      </li>
      <li>
        <strong>Publish:</strong> approved stories appear in Wall of Paths and the Jobs directory.
      </li>
      <li>
        <strong>Guide:</strong> readers use stories to compare paths before making decisions.
      </li>
    </ol>
  </section>

  <section class="promise panel">
    <h2>Our promise</h2>
    <p>
      We are not trying to rank jobs. We are trying to make choices less blind. If a story helps one
      student avoid a poor-fit path or discover a better one, it has done its job.
    </p>
    <div class="cta-row">
      <a class="btn btn-primary" href="/jobs">Explore stories</a>
      <a class="btn btn-secondary" href="/share">Contribute yours</a>
    </div>
  </section>
</Layout>

<style>
  .about-hero {
    position: relative;
    overflow: hidden;
  }

  .about-hero::after {
    content: '';
    position: absolute;
    inset: auto -12% -32% auto;
    width: 300px;
    height: 300px;
    border-radius: 999px;
    background: radial-gradient(circle, rgba(39, 130, 108, 0.18), rgba(39, 130, 108, 0));
    pointer-events: none;
  }

  .signal-strip {
    display: grid;
    gap: 0.6rem;
    margin: 0.6rem 0 1.2rem;
  }

  .signal-strip p {
    margin: 0;
    padding: 0.55rem 0.8rem;
    border: 1px solid var(--line);
    border-radius: 999px;
    background: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.66);
    color: var(--ink-soft);
  }

  .signal-strip span {
    display: inline-flex;
    margin-right: 0.45rem;
    padding: 0.08rem 0.35rem;
    border-radius: 999px;
    background: rgba(15, 76, 129, 0.12);
    color: var(--ink-strong);
    font-weight: 700;
    font-size: 0.82rem;
  }

  .origin-grid {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: 1.6fr 1fr;
    gap: 0.9rem;
    align-items: start;
  }

  .kicker {
    text-transform: uppercase;
    letter-spacing: 0.08em;
    font-size: 0.78rem;
    font-weight: 700;
    color: var(--ink-soft);
  }

  .origin-story h2,
  .compass h2,
  .promise h2,
  .review-panel h2 {
    margin: 0;
    line-height: 1.15;
  }

  .origin-story blockquote {
    margin: 0.9rem 0 0;
    padding: 0.7rem 0.85rem;
    border-left: 4px solid var(--brand-secondary);
    background: rgba(240, 139, 62, 0.08);
    border-radius: 10px;
    font-size: 1.05rem;
  }

  .review-panel dl {
    margin: 0;
    display: grid;
    gap: 0.65rem;
  }

  .review-panel dt {
    font-weight: 700;
  }

  .review-panel dd {
    margin: 0.18rem 0 0;
    color: var(--ink-soft);
  }

  .compass {
    margin-top: 0.9rem;
  }

  .compass-grid {
    display: grid;
    gap: 0.75rem;
    grid-template-columns: repeat(2, minmax(0, 1fr));
  }

  .compass-grid article {
    border: 1px dashed rgba(15, 42, 59, 0.32);
    border-radius: 12px;
    padding: 0.7rem;
    background: #fff;
  }

  .compass-grid h3 {
    margin: 0;
    font-size: 1rem;
  }

  .compass-grid p {
    margin: 0.4rem 0 0;
    color: var(--ink-soft);
  }

  .lifecycle {
    margin-top: 1rem;
  }

  .lifecycle ol {
    list-style: none;
    margin: 0.55rem 0 0;
    padding: 0;
    display: grid;
    gap: 0.65rem;
    counter-reset: lifecycle;
  }

  .lifecycle li {
    counter-increment: lifecycle;
    padding: 0.65rem 0.8rem 0.65rem 2.6rem;
    border: 1px solid var(--line);
    border-radius: 12px;
    background: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.72);
    color: var(--ink-soft);
    position: relative;
  }

  .lifecycle li::before {
    content: counter(lifecycle);
    position: absolute;
    left: 0.75rem;
    top: 0.58rem;
    width: 1.32rem;
    height: 1.32rem;
    border-radius: 999px;
    font-size: 0.82rem;
    font-weight: 700;
    display: inline-flex;
    align-items: center;
    justify-content: center;
    background: linear-gradient(140deg, var(--brand-primary), #0b6ab3);
    color: #f4fbff;
  }

  .promise {
    margin-top: 1rem;
    background:
      linear-gradient(140deg, rgba(15, 76, 129, 0.11), rgba(39, 130, 108, 0.12)), var(--bg-panel);
  }

  @media (max-width: 920px) {
    .origin-grid {
      grid-template-columns: 1fr;
    }
  }

  @media (max-width: 620px) {
    .compass-grid {
      grid-template-columns: 1fr;
    }

    .signal-strip p {
      border-radius: 14px;
    }
  }
</style>
